2. Installation Guides
2.1 System Requirements
[Define any system requirements necessary to support the application, including the software and relevant configurations]
2.1.1. Hardware Requirement:
The deployment environment requires two virtual machines forming a lightweight Kubernetes cluster using K3s. The cluster is composed of a control plane node responsible for cluster orchestration and a worker node dedicated to running application workloads.
VM1 - Control Plane Node:
•	Role: K3s Server (Control Plane) 
•	CPU: 6 cores 
•	RAM: 32 GB 
•	Operating System: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS 
•	Disk Capacity: ≥ 200 GiB (SSD) 
•	Required Open Ports (Inbound):
o	80 - HTTP 
o	443 - HTTPS 
o	6443 - Kubernetes API Server 
o	30037, 30038 - NodePort services (may vary depending on deployment configuration) 
VM2 - Worker Node:
•	Role: K3s Agent (Worker Node) 
•	CPU: 10 cores 
•	RAM: 96 GB 
•	Operating System: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS 
•	Disk Capacity: ≥ 200 GiB (SSD)
2.1.2. Network Requirement:
Both virtual machines must:
•	Be located within the same subnet (private network) 
•	Have private IP addresses and be able to communicate directly with each other 
•	Be able to ping each other (ICMP) and maintain stable TCP connectivity 
Mandatory requirements for network range (network isolation):
•	The private IP range of the VMs must not overlap with: 
o	Pod CIDR (default K3s: 10.42.0.0/16) 
o	Service CIDR (default K3s: 10.43.0.0/16) 
•	Recommendation: 
o	Use a dedicated infrastructure range, for example: 192.168.x.x or 172.16.x.x 
•	If the 10.x.x.x range must be used: 
o	The Pod CIDR and Service CIDR must be reconfigured during cluster initialization to avoid conflicts 
The network environment must also satisfy the following conditions:
•	Low latency between cluster nodes. 
•	Stable internal bandwidth to support container communication. 
•	No NAT or firewall rules should block internal traffic between cluster nodes.

